name: Pete Fowler | 300Kg Coffee
description:
Pete’s inspiration for his work comes from nature, daily life, psychedelica, monsters, music  and much more. Forming a backdrop to his ever growing family of characters and creatures, his work inhabits a world where character design meets music and art in a weird and wonderful way.

Pete was asked to illustrate the 300Kg of coffee used at DunneFrankowski during their first year at Protein

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Sichi | 2717 Espresso In & Out
description:
Sichi twiddles his thumbs in between creating character based illustrations alongside art directing and designing. Taking inspiration from the everyday people he spots hanging around in places they, and he, probably shouldn't be hanging around in. His style is reduced minimalistic simplicity with abstracted environmental elements and a dash of tasty cool. He draws and designs with digital tools and sometimes draws and paints with traditional materials in an ever growing pile of sketchbooks.

Sichi illustrated the total amount of espressos, both drink in and tak-away, served at DunneFrankowski during their first year at Protein

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Jamie Winder | 873 Liters Of Water
description:
Bangkok/London based graphic designer and print-maker. Screen printing allows Jamie time away from his Mac to get his hands dirty and indulge in bright colours, patterns and abstractions. Often geometric, typographic, or shaded with tight line work, Jamie's prints betray his vocation despite his best intentions.

Jamie, an old customer of Rob and Vic from their days at Tapped and Packed, was brought in to bring life to the 873 liters of water used to make all coffees at DunneFrankowski during their first year at Protein

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Tom J Newell | 1.333 Kg Caffeine
description:
Originating in Chesterfield, Derbyshire. Newell studied Fine Art in Sheffield. Since graduating as a conceptual artist, he began making more illustrative work in the form of gig posters for his friends bands. He went on to draw artwork for the likes of Daniel Johnston and MF DOOM and illustrations for Dazed & Confused. He is constantly inspired by Captain 
Beefheart.

Tom was given the task of realising the painfully toxic amount of Caffeine extracted at DunneFrankowski during their first year at Protein.

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Mr Steve McCarthy | 6063 Milk Coffee Out
description:
Mr Steve McCarthy is a freelance illustrator and designer working in Dublin. His first childrens book ‘Sally go round the stars’ was nominated for the Bord Gais childrens book of the year, he plans to continue producing children’s picture books, and seeks to continue using illustration in all manner of weird and wonderful projects. The above Illustration was inspired by "In the year 2525" by Zager & Evans.

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Shane Kenna | 42.415 Km Traveled By Barista In Espresso Service
description:
Dublin born, Kenna predominantly explores the many areas of graphic design, but preferably works within the fields of Branding, in-house illustration and personalized icon suites.

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Mark James | 617 Filter Papers
description:
An artist and graphic designer whose work focuses on art, music and fashion. His work includes art direction, video direction, photography, illustration, graphic and product design. Working in a variety of media, including sculpture, film and print. His conceptual work is inspired by a mix of popular culture and social commentary. 

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Mike Kilkelly | 2640 Calories Burnt By Barista During Espresso Service
description:
I draw about the gross and funny stuff in life - revolving around excessive partying, drinking and riding bikes. I watch a lot of cartoons. I love Ren & Stimpy, Beavis & Butthead and some old Warner Brothers cartoons (y'know, Foghorn Leghorn or whatever). My drawings are pretty much a mushed up blend of that humour and the grim reality 
of life… again the blood, vomit, booze and all that it means to be having awesome fun. 
I wanna work with cool people on sweet projects and have a good time all the time.

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Luis Lopez-Smith | 31.874 kilo Waste Milk Bottles
description:
After studying Mens fashion at Manchester met and Royal College of Art, Luis’ recent highlight was a commission to design and manufacture the Belize Olympic kit for London 2012. Currently starting his own label. 

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Lars K. Huse | 2204672 Coffee Beans
description:
Lars K. Huse is a young illustrator, artist and coffee-supergeek from Oslo, Norway. Currently based in the UK, he does illustration-work  under the moniker illustration and coffee. He is also a third of the Oslo- based coffee/design company Kaffikaze. One of his main areas of work is creating a renewed aesthetic for the specialty coffee industry based upon an informed approach. 

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Greg Eason | 31.874 kilo Waste Milk Bottles
description:
Greg Eason was born in Kent in 1985, and studied at Norwich University College of The Arts. He lives and works in East London, and is represented by The Contemporary London.

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: DesignGoat | 64.6 Kilo Paper Cups
description:
Designgoat are an industrial design studio based in Dublin. Set up in 2011 by Cian Corcoran & Ahmad Fakhry they have been working on a broad range of creative projects, from custom furniture, exhibition, interior and food design. They have been working for local and international clients on bespoke pieces and mass produced consumer products. They are interested in mixing their influences with their work, with a love for minimalism, music, food and great craftsmanship, they are obsessed with details . . . and coffee. 

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Dan Leo | Milk Coffee In 3910
description:
Uncontrollably doodling his way through the school, he went on to study Animation and Graphic design. Now spending his time perusing all things creative regardless of it being digital, hand painted, 3D or outside for the world to see. Most of his work is centred around an organic, fictitious world where the grotesque sits content along side beauty.
The aim is to create works that look as if they were created using vector software but have been painted by hand. 

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Jonathan E | 1526.5 litres Milk
description:
First appearing in ‘93 in Deadline and Tank Girl, Jonathan’s work in comic strips and illustration since has been used in countless publications. With his partner Felt Mistress (Louise Evans) his character work has taken on a third dimension, in the form of Louise’s hand crafted felt sculptures and his vinyl toy Inspector Cumulus.

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Ben Blake | Filter in 1826
description:
Grew up in Ohio, currently living in Bologna, Italy. I love coffee and want to learn as much as I can about it. I'm working on a project to doodle my way through coffee at drawcoffee.com.

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints

name: Luke Insect | 1442 Filter Out
description:
After studying Graphic Design & Illustration at Newcastle, Luke returned to London to work as a designer. Cutting his teeth artworking record sleeves for the likes of Funkadelic, Motorhead & Ozzy Osbourne. 

In 2007, Luke headed down to Brighton to set up his own boutique studio, focusing on design & illustration for the youth, fashion & music markets, aided by an ever-changing motley crew of workers ants.

Edition of 25 A2 giclee prints
